{"id":80164,"title":"Cutaneous larva migrans on the scalp: atypical presentation of a common disease.","abstract":"Cutaneous larva migrans is a pruritic dermatitis due to the inoculation of helminths larvae in the skin, and it often occurs in children in tropical and subtropical areas. The authors describe an atypical case of cutaneous larva migrans in a 11 year-old child with scalp involvement, an unusual topography for this lesion. ","date":"2014-04-28","categories":"Parasitic Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24770515","annotations":[{"name":"Larva","weight":0.813909,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larva"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.784197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.768313,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Itch","weight":0.722028,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Itch"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.695423,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Dermatitis","weight":0.623267,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatitis"},{"name":"Parasitic worm","weight":0.579861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parasitic_worm"},{"name":"Tropics","weight":0.443488,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropics"},{"name":"Inoculation","weight":0.355556,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inoculation"},{"name":"Subtropics","weight":0.179122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subtropics"},{"name":"Topography","weight":0.165475,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topography"},{"name":"Cutaneous larva migrans","weight":0.124145,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_larva_migrans"},{"name":"Scalp","weight":0.123431,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scalp"},{"name":"Child","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child"}]}
